---
// One idea: a spine re-punctuated — the same sentence, newly articulated.
---
<svg viewBox="0 0 600 240" role="img" aria-labelledby="artic-t">
  <title id="artic-t">A spine drawn as a line of vertebrae; between them sit punctuation marks — a comma, a colon, a caesura — showing the body as a sentence being re-punctuated.</title>
  <!-- the spine curve -->
  <path class="ink spine" d="M300 26 C 276 74, 320 108, 292 150 C 270 184, 312 200, 300 218" />
  <!-- vertebrae as beats -->
  <g class="ink block">
    <path d="M276 52 L 322 46" /><path d="M286 84 L 320 80" />
    <path d="M282 116 L 326 112" /><path d="M276 150 L 318 146" />
    <path d="M286 182 L 320 178" />
  </g>
  <!-- punctuation to the side, as annotation -->
  <text class="hand-label" x="360" y="58" font-size="22">,</text>
  <text class="hand-label" x="360" y="122" font-size="22">:</text>
  <text class="hand-label hand-label--accent" x="356" y="188" font-size="20">—</text>
  <path class="ink hair" d="M330 48 L 352 52 M328 112 L 352 116 M324 176 L 350 182" opacity="0.7" />
  <text class="hand-label" x="150" y="118" font-size="18">the same</text>
  <text class="hand-label" x="150" y="142" font-size="18">sentence,</text>
  <text class="hand-label hand-label--accent" x="150" y="170" font-size="18">re-punctuated</text>
</svg>
